cs.GT, cs.NE, cs.DS, cs.CC, cs.DM. 

This paper deals with the computational complexity and approximability of the network design problem for routing games, which is a topic in game theory and network optimization. Therefore, cs.GT (Game Theory) and cs.NE (Network Economics) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves analyzing the structure of the network and the paths taken by players, which suggests cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity) as likely sub-categories. Finally, the paper uses mathematical techniques to prove hardness results, which is a characteristic of cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics).
